97// CodeGenLLVM has members of type std::unique_ptr<T>. These members will be
98// instantiated in the constructor, which will requre that the type T is
99// complete at that point. Put the constructor (and destructor) here, since
100// all types should be complete here.
101CodeGenLLVM::CodeGenLLVM() = default;
102CodeGenLLVM::~CodeGenLLVM() = default;
103CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo::~DebugInfo() = default;
104
105std::unique_ptr<CodeGenLLVM> CodeGenLLVM::Create(LLVMTarget* llvm_target) {
106 std::string target = llvm_target->GetOrCreateTargetMachine()->getTarget().getName();
107 std::string factory_template = "tvm.codegen.llvm.target_";
108 void* handle = nullptr;
109 if (const PackedFunc* f = runtime::Registry::Get(factory_template + target)) {
110 handle = (*f)();
111 } else if (const PackedFunc* f = runtime::Registry::Get(factory_template + "cpu")) {
112 handle = (*f)();
113 } else {
114 LOG(FATAL) << "no factory function for codegen for target " << target;
115 }
116 if (handle) {
117 return std::unique_ptr<CodeGenLLVM>(static_cast<CodeGenLLVM*>(handle));
118 } else {
119 LOG(FATAL) << "unable to create codegen for target " << target;
120 return nullptr; // unreachable
121 }
122}
123
124void CodeGenLLVM::Init(const std::string& module_name, LLVMTarget* llvm_target, bool system_lib,
125 bool dynamic_lookup, bool target_c_runtime) {
126 llvm_target_ = llvm_target;
127 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
128 builder_.reset(new IRBuilder(*ctx));
129 module_.reset(new llvm::Module(module_name, *ctx));
130 md_builder_.reset(new llvm::MDBuilder(*ctx));
131 // types
132 t_void_ = llvm::Type::getVoidTy(*ctx);
133 t_void_p_ = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx)->getPointerTo(GetGlobalAddressSpace());
134 t_int_ = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(*ctx);
135 t_char_ = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx);
136 t_int8_ = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx);
137 t_int16_ = llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(*ctx);
138 t_int32_ = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(*ctx);
139 t_int64_ = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(*ctx);
140 t_float64_ = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(*ctx);
141 // meta data
142 md_very_likely_branch_ = md_builder_->createBranchWeights(1 << 20, 1);
143 md_tbaa_root_ = md_builder_->createTBAARoot("tvm-tbaa");
144 md_tbaa_alias_set_ = md_builder_->createTBAANode("tvm-alias", md_tbaa_root_);
145 InitTarget();
146}

148void CodeGenLLVM::SetFastMathFlags(llvm::FastMathFlags fmf) { builder_->setFastMathFlags(fmf); }
149
150void CodeGenLLVM::InitTarget() {
151 llvm::TargetMachine* tm = llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine();
152 module_->setTargetTriple(tm->getTargetTriple().str());
153 module_->setDataLayout(tm->createDataLayout());
154 data_layout_.reset(new llvm::DataLayout(module_.get()));
155 if (native_vector_bits_ == 0) {
156 const auto& arch = tm->getTargetTriple().getArch();
157 if (arch == llvm::Triple::x86_64) {
158 // for avx512
159 native_vector_bits_ = 512;
160 } else if (arch == llvm::Triple::x86) {
161 native_vector_bits_ = 256;
162 } else if (arch == llvm::Triple::arm || arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64) {
163 native_vector_bits_ = 128;
164 } else {
165 native_vector_bits_ = 128;
166 std::string arch_name = std::string(tm->getTargetTriple().getArchName());
167 LOG(WARNING) << "Set native vector bits to be 128 for " << arch_name;
168 }
169 }
170}

182void CodeGenLLVM::AddFunctionInternal(const PrimFunc& f, bool ret_void) {
183 this->InitFuncState();
184
185 ICHECK_EQ(f->buffer_map.size(), 0U)
186 << "Cannot codegen function with buffer_map, please lower them first";
187
188 std::vector<llvm::Type*> param_types;
189 is_restricted_ = f->HasNonzeroAttr(tir::attr::kNoAlias);
190 for (Var param : f->params) {
191 param_types.push_back(GetLLVMType(param));
192 if (!is_restricted_ && param.dtype().is_handle()) {
193 alias_var_set_.insert(param.get());
194 }
195 }
196 // TODO(tvm-team):
197 // Update the function type to respect the ret_type field of f.
198 // Once we allow more flexibility in the PrimFunc.
199 llvm::FunctionType* ftype =
200 llvm::FunctionType::get(ret_void ? t_void_ : t_int_, param_types, false);
201
202 auto global_symbol = f->GetAttr<String>(tvm::attr::kGlobalSymbol);
203 ICHECK(global_symbol.defined())
204 << "CodeGenLLVM: Expect PrimFunc to have the global_symbol attribute";
205 function_ = module_->getFunction(MakeStringRef(global_symbol.value()));
206 if (function_ == nullptr) {
207 function_ = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
208 MakeStringRef(global_symbol.value()), module_.get());
209 }
210 function_->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::C);
211 function_->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes::DLLExportStorageClass);
212 SetTargetAttributes(function_);
213
214 // set var map and align information
215 auto arg_it = function_->arg_begin();
216 for (size_t i = 0; i < f->params.size(); ++i, ++arg_it) {
217 llvm::Argument* v = &(*arg_it);
218 const Var& var = f->params[i];
219 var_map_[var.get()] = v;
220 v->setName(std::string(var->name_hint));
221 if (is_restricted_) {
222 if (var.dtype().is_handle() && !alias_var_set_.count(var.get())) {
223 // set non alias.
224#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
225 function_->addParamAttr(i, llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
226#else
227 function_->setDoesNotAlias(i + 1);
228#endif
229 }
230 }
231 }
232 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
233 llvm::BasicBlock* entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "entry", function_);
234 builder_->SetInsertPoint(entry);
235 this->VisitStmt(f->body);
236
237 // Add alignment attribute if needed.
238#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
239 for (size_t i = 0; i < f->params.size(); ++i) {
240 const Var& var = f->params[i];
241 auto f = alloc_storage_info_.find(var.get());
242 if (f != alloc_storage_info_.end()) {
243 unsigned align = f->second.alignment;
244 if (align > 1) {
245 auto attr = llvm::Attribute::get(*ctx, llvm::Attribute::Alignment, align);
246 function_->addParamAttr(i, attr);
247 }
248 }
249 }
250#endif
251
252 if (ret_void) {
253 builder_->CreateRetVoid();
254 } else {
255 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
256 }
257}
258
259std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> CodeGenLLVM::Finish() {
260 this->AddStartupFunction();
261 for (size_t i = 0; i < link_modules_.size(); ++i) {
262 ICHECK(!llvm::Linker::linkModules(*module_, std::move(link_modules_[i])))
263 << "Failed to link modules";
264 }
265 link_modules_.clear();
266 // optimize
267 this->Optimize();
268 return std::move(module_);
269}
270
271void CodeGenLLVM::HandleImport(const std::string& code) {
272 llvm::StringRef code_str(code);
273 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> mlib;
274 if (code_str.endswith(".ll") || code_str.endswith(".bc")) {
275 mlib = llvm_target_->GetInstance().LoadIR(code);
276 } else {
277 mlib = llvm_target_->GetInstance().ParseIR(code);
278 }
279
280 mlib->setTargetTriple(llvm_target_->GetTargetTriple());
281 mlib->setDataLayout(llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine()->createDataLayout());
282 // mark all the functions as force inline
283 for (llvm::Function& f : mlib->functions()) {
284 f.removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
285 f.addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
286 f.setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage);
287 }
288 // add to linker libraries.
289 this->AddLinkModule(std::move(mlib));
290}
291
292void CodeGenLLVM::AddLinkModule(std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>&& mod) {
293 link_modules_.emplace_back(std::move(mod));
294}

323void CodeGenLLVM::InitPassManagerBuilder(llvm::PassManagerBuilder* builder) {}
324
325void CodeGenLLVM::Optimize() {
326 // pass manager
327 FPassManager fpass(module_.get());
328 MPassManager mpass;
329 llvm::TargetMachine* tm = llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine();
330 mpass.add(llvm::createTargetTransformInfoWrapperPass(tm->getTargetIRAnalysis()));
331 fpass.add(llvm::createTargetTransformInfoWrapperPass(tm->getTargetIRAnalysis()));
332
333 // place optimization pass
334 llvm::PassManagerBuilder builder;
335
336 // Use the same opt-level as specified in TargetMachine for running passes
337 llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level opt_level = llvm_target_->GetOptLevel();
338
339 switch (opt_level) {
340 case llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level::None:
341 builder.OptLevel = 0;
342 break;
343 case llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level::Less:
344 builder.OptLevel = 1;
345 break;
346
347 case llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level::Default:
348 builder.OptLevel = 2;
349 break;
350
351 default:
352 // CodeGenOpt::Level::Aggressive
353 builder.OptLevel = 3;
354 }
355
356#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
357 builder.Inliner = llvm::createFunctionInliningPass(builder.OptLevel, 0, false);
358#else
359 builder.Inliner = llvm::createFunctionInliningPass(builder.OptLevel, 0);
360#endif
361 builder.LoopVectorize = true;
362 builder.SLPVectorize = true;
363 this->InitPassManagerBuilder(&builder);
364
365#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
366 tm->adjustPassManager(builder);
367#endif
368
369 builder.populateFunctionPassManager(fpass);
370 builder.populateModulePassManager(mpass);
371
372 fpass.doInitialization();
373 for (auto it = module_->begin(); it != module_->end(); ++it) {
374 fpass.run(*it);
375 }
376 fpass.doFinalization();
377 mpass.run(*module_);
378}

386llvm::Type* CodeGenLLVM::DTypeToLLVMType(const DataType& dtype) const {
387 if (dtype.is_handle()) {
388 ICHECK_EQ(dtype.lanes(), 1);
389 return t_void_p_;
390 }
391 if (dtype.is_void()) {
392 return t_void_;
393 }
394 llvm::Type* etype = nullptr;
395 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
396 if (dtype.is_int() || dtype.is_uint()) {
397 etype = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(*ctx, dtype.bits());
398 } else if (dtype.is_float()) {
399 switch (dtype.bits()) {
400 case 16:
401 etype = llvm::Type::getHalfTy(*ctx);
402 break;
403 case 32:
404 etype = llvm::Type::getFloatTy(*ctx);
405 break;
406 case 64:
407 etype = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(*ctx);
408 break;
409 default:
410 LOG(FATAL) << "do not support " << dtype;
411 }
412 }
413 if (dtype.lanes() != 1) {
414#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
415 return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(etype, dtype.lanes());
416#else
417 return llvm::VectorType::get(etype, dtype.lanes());
418#endif
419 } else {
420 return etype;
421 }
422} // namespace codegen
423
424llvm::Type* CodeGenLLVM::GetLLVMType(const Type& type) const {
425 if (auto* ptr = type.as<PrimTypeNode>()) {
426 return DTypeToLLVMType(ptr->dtype);
427 } else if (auto* ptr = type.as<PointerTypeNode>()) {
428 // LLVM IR doesn't allow void*, so we need to recognize this
429 // pattern explicitly.
430 if (auto* primtype = ptr->element_type.as<PrimTypeNode>()) {
431 if (primtype->dtype.is_void()) {
432 return t_void_p_;
433 }
434 }
435 // TODO(tvm-team) consider put storage scope into the pointer type.
436 return GetLLVMType(ptr->element_type)->getPointerTo(GetGlobalAddressSpace());
437 } else if (IsVoidType(type)) {
438 return t_void_;
439 } else {
440 LOG(FATAL) << "Type " << type << " does not have a corresponding LLVM Type";
441 return t_void_;
442 }
443}
444
445llvm::Type* CodeGenLLVM::GetLLVMType(const PrimExpr& expr) const {
446 return GetLLVMType(GetType(expr));
447}

449// Add tbaa alias information for load
450//
451// use a binary tree typed system to declare information
452// and allow alias to be distinguished across nodes.
453//
454// This trick comes from Halide's CodeGen_LLVM
455//
456void CodeGenLLVM::AddAliasInfo(llvm::Instruction* inst, const VarNode* buffer_var, PrimExpr index,
457 DataType access_dtype) {
458 if (alias_var_set_.count(buffer_var) != 0) {
459 // Mark all possibly aliased pointer as same type.
460 llvm::MDNode* meta = md_tbaa_alias_set_;
461 inst->setMetadata("tbaa", md_builder_->createTBAAStructTagNode(meta, meta, 0));
462 return;
463 }
464
465 int64_t base = 0, width = 0;
466 arith::PVar<IntImm> pbase, pstride;
467 arith::PVar<int> planes;
468 // create meta-data for alias analysis
469 // Use a group of binary tree ranges of memory banks.
470 int64_t xwith = 0;
471 if (arith::ramp(pbase, pstride, planes).Match(index)) {
472 base = pbase.Eval()->value;
473 xwith = planes.Eval() * pstride.Eval()->value;
474 } else if (auto* ptr = index.as<tir::IntImmNode>()) {
475 base = ptr->value;
476 xwith = 1;
477 }
478 // adjust address index unit to byte
479 const int64_t unit_bit_width = 8;
480 const int64_t access_elem_bits = access_dtype.bits() * access_dtype.lanes();
481 base = base * access_elem_bits / unit_bit_width;
482 xwith = (xwith * access_elem_bits + unit_bit_width - 1) / unit_bit_width;
483 if (xwith > 0) {
484 width = 1;
485 while (width < xwith) {
486 width *= 2;
487 }
488 while (base % width) {
489 base -= base % width;
490 width *= 2;
491 }
492 }
493
494 llvm::MDNode* meta = md_tbaa_root_;
495 std::ostringstream buffer_addr;
496 buffer_addr << buffer_var;
497 meta = md_builder_->createTBAAScalarTypeNode(buffer_addr.str(), meta);
498
499 // create a tree-shape access structure.
500 if (width != 0) {
501 for (int64_t w = 1024; w >= width; w /= 2) {
502 int64_t b = (base / w) * w;
503 std::stringstream os;
504 os << buffer_var << ".w" << w << ".b" << b;
505 meta = md_builder_->createTBAAScalarTypeNode(os.str(), meta);
506 }
507 }
508 inst->setMetadata("tbaa", md_builder_->createTBAAStructTagNode(meta, meta, 0));
509}

511void CodeGenLLVM::GetAlignment(DataType t, const VarNode* buf_var, const PrimExpr& index,
512 int* p_alignment, int* p_native_bits) {
513 int max_align_bits = t.bits();
514 auto it = alloc_storage_info_.find(buf_var);
515 if (it != alloc_storage_info_.end()) {
516 const StorageInfo& info = it->second;
517 *p_native_bits =
518 NativeVectorBits(runtime::StorageScope::Create(GetPtrStorageScope(GetRef<Var>(buf_var))));
519 max_align_bits = info.alignment * 8;
520 } else {
521 *p_native_bits = native_vector_bits_;
522 }
523
524 arith::ModularSet me = analyzer_->modular_set(index);
525 int64_t base = me->base;
526 int64_t coeff = me->coeff;
527
528 int align_bits = t.bits();
529 while (align_bits < max_align_bits && base % 2 == 0 && coeff % 2 == 0) {
530 base = base / 2;
531 coeff = coeff / 2;
532 align_bits *= 2;
533 }
534 if (align_bits < 8) {
535 align_bits = 8;
536 }
537 *p_alignment = align_bits / 8;
538}

540llvm::GlobalVariable* CodeGenLLVM::AllocateSharedMemory(DataType dtype, size_t size,
541 unsigned int shared_address_space,
542 int alignment,
543 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes linkage) {
544 llvm::Type* type = llvm::ArrayType::get(DTypeToLLVMType(dtype), size);
545 llvm::GlobalVariable* global =
546 new llvm::GlobalVariable(*module_, type, false, linkage, nullptr, "shmem", nullptr,
547 llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal, shared_address_space);
548#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
549 global->setAlignment(llvm::Align(alignment));
550#else
551 global->setAlignment(alignment);
552#endif
553 return global;
554}

556std::unique_ptr<CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo> CodeGenLLVM::CreateDebugInfo(llvm::Module* module) {
557#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
558 auto debug_info = std::make_unique<CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo>();
559 debug_info->di_builder_ = std::make_unique<llvm::DIBuilder>(*module);
560#else
561 auto debug_info = llvm::make_unique<CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo>();
562 debug_info->di_builder_ = llvm::make_unique<llvm::DIBuilder>(*module);
563#endif
564 // TODO(tulloch): pass this information through relay::Span classes to the IRModule instance?
565 debug_info->file_ = debug_info->di_builder_->createFile("model.tvm", "/tmp/");
566 debug_info->compilation_unit_ = debug_info->di_builder_->createCompileUnit(
567 llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C, debug_info->file_, "TVM", 0, "", 0, "",
568 llvm::DICompileUnit::DebugEmissionKind::FullDebug,
569 /* SplitDebugInlining */ true,
570 /* DebugInfoForProfiling */ true);
571 return debug_info;
572}

574llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateBroadcast(llvm::Value* value, int lanes) {
575#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
576 llvm::Type* type = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(value->getType(), lanes);
577#else
578 llvm::Type* type = llvm::VectorType::get(value->getType(), lanes);
579#endif
580 llvm::Constant* undef = llvm::UndefValue::get(type);
581 llvm::Constant* zero = ConstInt32(0);
582 value = builder_->CreateInsertElement(undef, value, zero);
583#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 120
584 llvm::Constant* mask = llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(llvm::ElementCount::getFixed(lanes), zero);
585#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
586 llvm::Constant* mask =
587 llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(llvm::ElementCount(lanes, /*Scalable=*/false), zero);
588#else
589 llvm::Constant* mask = llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(lanes, zero);
590#endif
591 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(value, undef, mask);
592}
593
594llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecSlice(llvm::Value* vec, int begin, int extent) {
595 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(vec);
596 if (extent == num_elems && begin == 0) return vec;
597 ICHECK(begin >= 0 && extent <= num_elems) << "Slicing out of bound!\n";
598 std::vector<llvm::Constant*> indices;
599 indices.reserve(extent);
600 for (int i = 0; i < extent; ++i) {
601 if (begin + i >= 0 && begin + i < num_elems) {
602 indices.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(t_int32_, begin + i));
603 } else {
604 indices.push_back(llvm::UndefValue::get(t_int32_));
605 }
606 }
607 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(vec, vec, llvm::ConstantVector::get(indices));
608}
609
610llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecFlip(llvm::Value* vec) {
611 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(vec);
612#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
613 std::vector<int> indices;
614#else
615 std::vector<unsigned> indices;
616#endif
617 for (int i = 0; i < num_elems; ++i) {
618 indices.push_back(num_elems - i - 1);
619 }
620 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(vec, vec, indices);
621}
622
623llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecPad(llvm::Value* vec, int target_lanes) {
624 llvm::Value* mask = llvm::UndefValue::get(DTypeToLLVMType(DataType::Int(32, target_lanes)));
625 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(vec);
626 if (num_elems == target_lanes) return vec;
627 ICHECK_LT(num_elems, target_lanes);
628 for (int i = 0; i < num_elems; ++i) {
629 mask = builder_->CreateInsertElement(mask, ConstInt32(i), ConstInt32(i));
630 }
631 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(vec, vec, mask);
632}
633
634llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecConcat(std::vector<llvm::Value*> vecs) {
635 // To allow creating vectors from scalars, convert any scalars in "vecs" to single-lane
636 // LLVM vector types.
637 for (size_t i = 0, e = vecs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
638 llvm::Value* v = vecs[i];
639 if (!v->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
640#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
641 llvm::Type* vec_ty = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(v->getType(), 1);
642#else
643 llvm::Type* vec_ty = llvm::VectorType::get(v->getType(), 1);
644#endif
645 vecs[i] = builder_->CreateInsertElement(llvm::UndefValue::get(vec_ty), v, ConstInt32(0));
646 }
647 }
648
649 // concat vector, tree shape reduction
650 int total_lanes = 0;
651
652 for (llvm::Value* v : vecs) {
653 total_lanes += GetVectorNumElements(v);
654 }
655 while (vecs.size() > 1) {
656 std::vector<llvm::Value*> new_vecs;
657 for (size_t i = 0; i < vecs.size() - 1; i += 2) {
658 llvm::Value* lhs = vecs[i];
659 llvm::Value* rhs = vecs[i + 1];
660 const size_t lhs_lanes = GetVectorNumElements(lhs);
661 const size_t rhs_lanes = GetVectorNumElements(rhs);
662 if (lhs_lanes < rhs_lanes) {
663 lhs = CreateVecPad(lhs, rhs_lanes);
664 } else if (rhs_lanes < lhs_lanes) {
665 rhs = CreateVecPad(rhs, lhs_lanes);
666 }
667 const size_t shared_lanes = std::max(lhs_lanes, rhs_lanes);
668#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
669 std::vector<int> mask;
670#else
671 std::vector<unsigned> mask;
672#endif
673 for (size_t i = 0; i < lhs_lanes; ++i) {
674 mask.push_back(i);
675 }
676 for (size_t i = 0; i < rhs_lanes; ++i) {
677 mask.push_back(shared_lanes + i);
678 }
679 new_vecs.push_back(builder_->CreateShuffleVector(lhs, rhs, mask));
680 }
681 if (vecs.size() % 2 != 0) {
682 new_vecs.push_back(vecs.back());
683 }
684 vecs.swap(new_vecs);
685 }
686 return CreateVecSlice(vecs[0], 0, total_lanes);
687}
688
689void CodeGenLLVM::CreateSerialFor(llvm::Value* begin, llvm::Value* end, llvm::Value* stride,
690 const Var& loop_var, const Stmt& body) {
691 llvm::BasicBlock* pre_block = builder_->GetInsertBlock();
692 std::string loop_var_name = loop_var->name_hint;
693 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
694 auto* for_begin = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "for_begin_" + loop_var_name, function_);
695 auto* for_body = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "for_body_" + loop_var_name, function_);
696 auto* for_end = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "for_end_" + loop_var_name, function_);
697 builder_->CreateBr(for_begin);
698 builder_->SetInsertPoint(for_begin);
699 llvm::PHINode* loop_value = builder_->CreatePHI(begin->getType(), 2);
700 loop_value->setName(loop_var->name_hint.c_str());
701 loop_value->addIncoming(begin, pre_block);
702 ICHECK(!var_map_.count(loop_var.get()));
703 var_map_[loop_var.get()] = loop_value;
704 builder_->CreateCondBr(CreateLT(loop_var.dtype(), loop_value, end), for_body, for_end,
705 md_very_likely_branch_);
706 builder_->SetInsertPoint(for_body);
707 this->VisitStmt(body);
708 var_map_.erase(loop_var.get());
709 llvm::Value* loop_next = CreateAdd(loop_var.dtype(), loop_value, stride);
710 loop_value->addIncoming(loop_next, builder_->GetInsertBlock());
711 builder_->CreateBr(for_begin);
712 builder_->SetInsertPoint(for_end);
713}
714
715// cast operatpr
716llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateCast(DataType from, DataType to, llvm::Value* value) {
717 llvm::Type* target = DTypeToLLVMType(to);
718 if (value->getType() == target) return value;
719 if (to.is_handle()) {
720 return builder_->CreateBitCast(value, target);
721 } else if (to.is_uint() && to.bits() == 1) {
722 if (from.is_float()) {
723 llvm::Constant* zero = llvm::ConstantFP::get(DTypeToLLVMType(from), 0.);
724 return builder_->CreateFCmpONE(value, zero);
725 } else {
726 llvm::Constant* zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(DTypeToLLVMType(from), 0);
727 return builder_->CreateICmpNE(value, zero);
728 }
729 } else if (!from.is_float() && !to.is_float()) {
730 return builder_->CreateIntCast(value, target, from.is_int());
731 } else if (from.is_float() && to.is_int()) {
732 return builder_->CreateFPToSI(value, target);
733 } else if (from.is_float() && to.is_uint()) {
734 if (to.bits() < 8) {
735 value = builder_->CreateFPToUI(value, DTypeToLLVMType(to.with_bits(8)));
736 return builder_->CreateIntCast(value, target, false);
737 } else {
738 return builder_->CreateFPToUI(value, target);
739 }
740 } else if (from.is_int() && to.is_float()) {
741 return builder_->CreateSIToFP(value, target);
742 } else if (from.is_uint() && to.is_float()) {
743 return builder_->CreateUIToFP(value, target);
744 } else {
745 ICHECK(from.is_float() && to.is_float());
746 return builder_->CreateFPCast(value, target);
747 }
748}

750llvm::Constant* CodeGenLLVM::GetGlobalConstant(llvm::Constant* const_data, const std::string& name,
751 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes linkage_type) {
752 llvm::Type* ty = const_data->getType();
753 llvm::GlobalVariable* global =
754 new llvm::GlobalVariable(*module_, ty, true, linkage_type, const_data, name);
755#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
756 global->setAlignment(llvm::Align(1));
757#else
758 global->setAlignment(1);
759#endif
760 llvm::Constant* zero = ConstInt32(0);
761 llvm::Constant* indices[] = {zero, zero};
762 llvm::Constant* ptr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(ty, global, indices);
763 return ptr;
764}

775CodeGenLLVM::TypedPointer CodeGenLLVM::CreateBufferPtr(llvm::Value* buffer_ptr,
776 DataType buffer_element_dtype,
777 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Value*> indices,
778 DataType value_dtype) {
779 ICHECK_EQ(indices.size(), 1) << "CodeGenLLVM requires all buffers to be flat 1-d buffers.";
780 llvm::Value* index = indices[0];
781
782 llvm::PointerType* buffer_ptr_type = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(buffer_ptr->getType());
783 ICHECK(buffer_ptr_type != nullptr);
784 auto address_space = buffer_ptr_type->getAddressSpace();
785
786 llvm::Type* element_type = DTypeToLLVMType(buffer_element_dtype);
787 llvm::PointerType* element_ptr_type =
788 DTypeToLLVMType(buffer_element_dtype)->getPointerTo(address_space);
789 llvm::Type* value_type = DTypeToLLVMType(value_dtype);
790 llvm::PointerType* value_ptr_type = value_type->getPointerTo(address_space);
791
792 ICHECK(index->getType()->isIntegerTy()) << "Expected buffer index to be an integer";
793
794 if (buffer_ptr_type != element_ptr_type) {
795 buffer_ptr = builder_->CreatePointerCast(buffer_ptr, element_ptr_type);
796 }
797 ICHECK(!HasAlignmentPadding(buffer_element_dtype))
798 << "DType " << buffer_element_dtype
799 << " has padding for alignment. TVM data arrays are expected to be densely packed, with no "
800 "padding for alignment.";
801 llvm::Value* value_ptr = builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(element_type, buffer_ptr, index);
802
803 if (element_ptr_type != value_ptr_type) {
804 value_ptr = builder_->CreatePointerCast(value_ptr, value_ptr_type);
805 }
806
807 return TypedPointer(value_type, value_ptr);
808}

810llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::GetVarValue(const VarNode* v) const {
811 auto it = var_map_.find(v);
812 ICHECK(it != var_map_.end()) << "cannot find variable " << v->name_hint;
813 return it->second;

816void CodeGenLLVM::CreatePrintf(const std::string& format,
817 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Value*> format_args) {
818 llvm::Function* func_printf = module_->getFunction("printf");
819 if (func_printf == nullptr) {
820 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int32_, true);
821 func_printf =
822 llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, "printf", module_.get());
823 }
824
825 llvm::Function* func_fflush = module_->getFunction("fflush");
826 if (!func_fflush) {
827 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int32_, {t_void_p_}, false);
828 func_fflush =
829 llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, "fflush", module_.get());
830 }
831
832 llvm::Value* str = builder_->CreateGlobalStringPtr(format);
833 str->setName("printf_format_str");
834
835 std::vector<llvm::Value*> printf_args = {str};
836 printf_args.insert(printf_args.end(), format_args.begin(), format_args.end());
837 builder_->CreateCall(func_printf, printf_args);
838
839 // Call fflush() immediately, as this utility is intended for debug
840 // purposes. A segfault occurring within the generated LLVM code
841 // would otherwise leave the stdout buffer unflushed.
842 llvm::Value* null_stream = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(t_void_p_);
843 null_stream->setName("null_stream");
844 builder_->CreateCall(func_fflush, {null_stream});
845}

847llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateLookupReturnAddress(unsigned int level) {
848 llvm::Value* level_val = llvm::ConstantInt::get(t_int32_, level);
849 llvm::Function* builtin =
850 llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module_.get(), llvm::Intrinsic::returnaddress);
851 llvm::Value* call = builder_->CreateCall(builtin, level_val);
852 call->setName("return_addr");
853
854 return call;
855}

857llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateCallExtern(Type ret_type, String global_symbol,
858 const Array<PrimExpr>& args, bool skip_first_arg) {
859 std::vector<llvm::Value*> arg_value;
860 std::vector<llvm::Type*> arg_type;
861 for (size_t i = static_cast<size_t>(skip_first_arg); i < args.size(); ++i) {
862 arg_value.push_back(MakeValue(args[i]));
863 arg_type.push_back(arg_value.back()->getType());
864 }
865 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(GetLLVMType(ret_type), arg_type, false);
866 llvm::Function* f = module_->getFunction(MakeStringRef(global_symbol));
867 if (f == nullptr) {
868 f = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, MakeStringRef(global_symbol),
869 module_.get());
870 }
871 llvm::CallInst* call = builder_->CreateCall(f, arg_value);
872 return call;
873}

875llvm::Function* CodeGenLLVM::GetIntrinsicDecl(llvm::Intrinsic::ID id, llvm::Type* ret_type,
876 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> arg_types) {
877 llvm::Module* module = module_.get();
878
879 if (!llvm::Intrinsic::isOverloaded(id)) {
880 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, {});
881 }
882
883 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Intrinsic::IITDescriptor, 4> infos;
884 llvm::Intrinsic::getIntrinsicInfoTableEntries(id, infos);
885 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 4> overload_types;
886
887#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
888 auto try_match = [&](llvm::FunctionType* f_ty, bool var_arg) {
889 overload_types.clear();
890 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Intrinsic::IITDescriptor> ref(infos);
891 auto match = llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicSignature(f_ty, ref, overload_types);
892 if (match == llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_Match) {
893 bool error = llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicVarArg(var_arg, ref);
894 if (error) {
895 return llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchArg;
896 }
897 }
898 return match;
899 };
900
901 // First, try matching the signature assuming non-vararg case.
902 auto* fn_ty = llvm::FunctionType::get(ret_type, arg_types, false);
903 switch (try_match(fn_ty, false)) {
904 case llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchRet:
905 // The return type doesn't match, there is nothing else to do.
906 return nullptr;
907 case llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_Match:
908 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, overload_types);
909 case llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchArg:
910 break;
911 }
912
913 // Keep adding one type at a time (starting from empty list), and
914 // try matching the vararg signature.
915 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 4> var_types;
916 for (int i = 0, e = arg_types.size(); i <= e; ++i) {
917 if (i > 0) var_types.push_back(arg_types[i - 1]);
918 auto* ft = llvm::FunctionType::get(ret_type, var_types, true);
919 if (try_match(ft, true) == llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_Match) {
920 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, overload_types);
921 }
922 }
923 // Failed to identify the type.
924 return nullptr;
925
926#else // TVM_LLVM_VERSION
927 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Intrinsic::IITDescriptor> ref(infos);
928 // matchIntrinsicType returns true on error.
929 if (llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicType(ret_type, ref, overload_types)) {
930 return nullptr;
931 }
932 for (llvm::Type* t : arg_types) {
933 if (llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicType(t, ref, overload_types)) {
934 return nullptr;
935 }
936 }
937 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, overload_types);
938#endif // TVM_LLVM_VERSION
939}

952llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateIntrinsic(const CallNode* op) {
953 if (op->op.same_as(builtin_call_llvm_intrin_) || op->op.same_as(builtin_call_llvm_pure_intrin_)) {
954 ICHECK_GE(op->args.size(), 2U);
955 llvm::Intrinsic::ID id = static_cast<llvm::Intrinsic::ID>(Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[0])->value);
956 int64_t num_signature = Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[1])->value;
957 std::vector<llvm::Value*> arg_value;
958 std::vector<llvm::Type*> arg_type;
959 for (size_t i = 2; i < op->args.size(); ++i) {
960 arg_value.push_back(MakeValue(op->args[i]));
961 if (i - 2 < static_cast<size_t>(num_signature)) {
962 arg_type.push_back(arg_value.back()->getType());
963 }
964 }
965 // LLVM's prefetch intrinsic returns "void", while TVM's prefetch
966 // returns int32. This causes problems because prefetch is one of
967 // those intrinsics that is generated automatically via the
968 // tvm.intrin.rule mechanism. Any other intrinsic with a type
969 // mismatch will have to be treated specially here.
970 // TODO(kparzysz-quic): fix this once TVM prefetch uses the same
971 // type as LLVM.
972 llvm::Type* return_type =
973 (id != llvm::Intrinsic::prefetch) ? GetLLVMType(GetRef<PrimExpr>(op)) : t_void_;
974 llvm::Function* f = GetIntrinsicDecl(id, return_type, arg_type);
975 ICHECK(f) << "Cannot find intrinsic declaration, possible type mismatch: "
976#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 130
977 << llvm::Intrinsic::getBaseName(id).str();
978#else
979 << llvm::Intrinsic::getName(id, {});
980#endif
981 return builder_->CreateCall(f, arg_value);
982 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_and())) {
983 return builder_->CreateAnd(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
984 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_or())) {
985 return builder_->CreateOr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
986 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_not())) {
987 return builder_->CreateNot(MakeValue(op->args[0]));
988 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_xor())) {
989 return builder_->CreateXor(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
990 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::shift_left())) {
991 return builder_->CreateShl(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
992 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::shift_right())) {
993 if (op->args[0].dtype().is_int()) {
994 return builder_->CreateAShr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
995 } else {
996 return builder_->CreateLShr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
997 }
998 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_storage_sync())) {
999 return CreateStorageSync(op);
1000 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::address_of())) {
1001 const BufferLoadNode* load = op->args[0].as<BufferLoadNode>();
1002 ICHECK(op->args.size() == 1 && load);
1003
1004 Array<PrimExpr> indices = load->indices;
1005 if (const RampNode* r = indices[indices.size() - 1].as<RampNode>()) {
1006 indices.Set(indices.size() - 1, r->base);
1007 }
1008
1009 std::vector<llvm::Value*> indices_val;
1010 for (const auto& index : indices) {
1011 indices_val.push_back(MakeValue(index));
1012 }
1013
1014 TypedPointer buffer_ptr = CreateBufferPtr(MakeValue(load->buffer->data), load->buffer->dtype,
1015 indices_val, load->dtype);
1016 unsigned addrspace =
1017 llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(buffer_ptr.addr->getType())->getAddressSpace();
1018 return builder_->CreatePointerCast(buffer_ptr.addr, t_char_->getPointerTo(addrspace));
1019 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::reinterpret()) && is_zero(op->args[0])) {
1020 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(t_void_p_);
1021 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::isnullptr())) {
1022 return builder_->CreateIsNull(MakeValue(op->args[0]));
1023 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::large_uint_imm())) {
1024 ICHECK_EQ(op->args.size(), 2U);
1025 uint64_t low = static_cast<uint64_t>(Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[0])->value);
1026 uint64_t high = static_cast<uint64_t>(Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[1])->value);
1027 uint64_t val = (high << 32U) | low;
1028 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype), val);
1029 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::if_then_else())) {
1030 ICHECK_EQ(op->args[0].dtype().lanes(), 1) << "if_then_else can only take scalar condition";
1031 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1032 auto* then_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_then", function_);
1033 auto* else_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_else", function_);
1034 auto* end_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_end", function_);
1035 builder_->CreateCondBr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), then_block, else_block);
1036 builder_->SetInsertPoint(then_block);
1037 llvm::Value* then_value = MakeValue(op->args[1]);
1038 llvm::BasicBlock* then_value_block = builder_->GetInsertBlock();
1039 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1040 builder_->SetInsertPoint(else_block);
1041 llvm::Value* else_value = MakeValue(op->args[2]);
1042 llvm::BasicBlock* else_value_block = builder_->GetInsertBlock();
1043 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1044 builder_->SetInsertPoint(end_block);
1045 llvm::PHINode* value = builder_->CreatePHI(then_value->getType(), 2);
1046 value->addIncoming(then_value, then_value_block);
1047 value->addIncoming(else_value, else_value_block);
1048 return value;
1049 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::ret())) {
1050 auto const* val = op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>();
1051 ICHECK(val) << "the tir.ret should be transformed to return zero "
1052 << "before the llvm code generation.";
1053 ICHECK_EQ(val->value, 0) << "the tir.ret should be transformed to "
1054 << "return zero before the llvm code generation.";
1055 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
1056 // LLVM allows exactly one terminator in a single basic block
1057 // append a new dummy basic block to avoid error.
1058 llvm::BasicBlock* ret_dummy =
1059 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), "ret_dummy", function_);
1060 builder_->SetInsertPoint(ret_dummy);
1061 return ret_dummy;
1062 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::reinterpret())) {
1063 llvm::Type* target = DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype);
1064 return builder_->CreateBitCast(MakeValue(op->args[0]), target);
1065 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::isnan())) {
1066 // TODO(hgt312): set fast math flag
1067 llvm::Value* a = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1068 return builder_->CreateFCmpUNO(a, a);
1069 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::vectorlow())) {
1070 llvm::Value* v = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1071 int l = GetVectorNumElements(v);
1072 return CreateVecSlice(v, 0, l / 2);
1073 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::vectorhigh())) {
1074 llvm::Value* v = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1075 int l = GetVectorNumElements(v);
1076 return CreateVecSlice(v, l / 2, l / 2);
1077 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::vectorcombine())) {
1078 llvm::Value* v0 = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1079 llvm::Value* v1 = MakeValue(op->args[1]);
1080 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(v0) * 2;
1081#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1082 std::vector<int> indices;
1083#else
1084 std::vector<unsigned> indices;
1085#endif
1086 for (int i = 0; i < num_elems; ++i) {
1087 indices.push_back(i);
1088 }
1089 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(v0, v1, indices);
1090 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::atomic_add())) {
1091 // TODO(masahi): Support atomic for CPU backend
1092 LOG(FATAL) << "CPU backend does not support atomic add yet.";
1093 return nullptr;
1094 } else {
1095 LOG(FATAL) << "unknown intrinsic " << op->op;
1096 return nullptr;
1097 }
1098}

1100void CodeGenLLVM::Scalarize(const PrimExpr& e, std::function<void(int i, llvm::Value* v)> f) {
1101 if (const RampNode* ramp = e.as<RampNode>()) {
1102 for (int i = 0; i < ramp->dtype.lanes(); ++i) {
1103 PrimExpr offset = ramp->base + (ramp->stride * i);
1104 f(i, MakeValue(offset));
1105 }
1106 } else {
1107 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(e);
1108 for (int i = 0; i < e.dtype().lanes(); ++i) {
1109 f(i, builder_->CreateExtractElement(value, i));
1110 }
1111 }
1112}

1272bool CodeGenLLVM::HasAlignmentPadding(DataType dtype) {
1273 const llvm::DataLayout& data_layout = module_->getDataLayout();
1274 int bytes = data_layout.getTypeAllocSize(DTypeToLLVMType(dtype));
1275 int bytes_scalar = data_layout.getTypeAllocSize(DTypeToLLVMType(dtype.element_of()));
1276 return bytes != bytes_scalar * dtype.lanes();
1277}

1279void CodeGenLLVM::BufferAccessHelper(
1280 Buffer buffer, Array<PrimExpr> indices, DataType value_dtype,
1281 std::function<llvm::Instruction*(TypedPointer buffer_ptr, int subelement_i, int alignment,
1282 bool is_volatile)>
1283 make_instruction) {
1284 DataType buffer_element_dtype = buffer->dtype;
1285
1286 ICHECK_GE(indices.size(), 1)
1287 << "Buffer " << buffer->name << " is accessed with no indices. "
1288 << "0-d scalar buffers are expected to be flattened to 1-d buffers prior to codegen.";
1289
1290 // Only the last index is allowed to be multi-lane. All earlier
1291 // indices must be scalar. This only matters for subclasses of
1292 // CodeGenLLVM, because the default implementation of GetBufferPtr
1293 // requires 1-d indices.
1294 std::vector<llvm::Value*> earlier_index_values;
1295 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices.size() - 1; i++) {
1296 ICHECK_EQ(indices[i].dtype().lanes(), 1)
1297 << "Buffer " << buffer->name << " is accessed with a multi-lane index at position " << i
1298 << ". Multi-lane indices are only supported as the last index.";
1299 earlier_index_values.push_back(MakeValue(indices[i]));
1300 }
1301
1302 PrimExpr last_index = indices[indices.size() - 1];
1303 ICHECK_EQ(value_dtype.lanes(), last_index.dtype().lanes() * buffer_element_dtype.lanes());
1304
1305 // Record index and elemtype in original form used for alias info
1306 PrimExpr last_index_origin = last_index;
1307 DataType buffer_element_dtype_origin = buffer_element_dtype;
1308
1309 bool is_volatile = volatile_buf_.count(buffer->data.get());
1310
1311 // If the buffer index is a contiguous ramp node, we only need to
1312 // access the first element, then cast to the value type.
1313 if (const RampNode* ramp_index = last_index.as<RampNode>()) {
1314 if (is_one(ramp_index->stride)) {
1315 last_index = ramp_index->base;
1316 }
1317 }
1318
1319 // All TVM arrays are densely packed. If the vectorized LLVM type
1320 // contains padding for alignment, we need to index based on the
1321 // size of the scalar type to avoid introducing that padding.
1322 if (last_index.dtype().lanes() == 1 && HasAlignmentPadding(buffer_element_dtype)) {
1323 last_index = buffer_element_dtype.lanes() * last_index;
1324 buffer_element_dtype = buffer_element_dtype.element_of();
1325 }
1326
1327 int alignment;
1328 if (last_index.dtype().lanes() == 1) {
1329 // If we are accessing with a single index, then the vectorized
1330 // element being accessed may require more alignment than the
1331 // underlying data type.
1332 int native_bits;
1333 GetAlignment(value_dtype, buffer->data.get(), last_index, &alignment, &native_bits);
1334 } else {
1335 // Otherwise, alignment is based on the return value's scalar
1336 // type.
1337 ICHECK_GE(value_dtype.bits(), 8);
1338 alignment = value_dtype.bits() / 8;
1339 }
1340
1341 llvm::Value* cached_vector_index = nullptr;
1342 for (int i = 0; i < last_index.dtype().lanes(); ++i) {
1343 llvm::Value* last_index_value;
1344 int subelement_i = i;
1345 if (const RampNode* ramp = last_index.as<RampNode>()) {
1346 PrimExpr offset = ramp->base + (ramp->stride * i);
1347 last_index_value = MakeValue(offset);
1348 } else if (last_index.dtype().lanes() > 1) {
1349 if (i == 0) {
1350 cached_vector_index = MakeValue(last_index);
1351 }
1352 last_index_value = builder_->CreateExtractElement(cached_vector_index, i);
1353 } else {
1354 last_index_value = MakeValue(last_index);
1355 subelement_i = -1;
1356 }
1357
1358 std::vector<llvm::Value*> all_index_values = earlier_index_values;
1359 all_index_values.push_back(last_index_value);
1360
1361 TypedPointer buffer_ptr =
1362 CreateBufferPtr(MakeValue(buffer->data), buffer_element_dtype, all_index_values,
1363 value_dtype.with_lanes(value_dtype.lanes() / last_index.dtype().lanes()));
1364 auto instruction = make_instruction(buffer_ptr, subelement_i, alignment, is_volatile);
1365 AddAliasInfo(instruction, buffer->data.get(), last_index_origin, buffer_element_dtype_origin);
1366 }
1367}

1369llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) {
1370 DataType value_dtype = op->dtype;
1371
1372 std::vector<llvm::Value*> loads;
1373
1374 auto make_load = [this, &loads](TypedPointer buffer_ptr, int /* subelement_i */, int alignment,
1375 bool is_volatile) {
1376#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1377 auto load = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(buffer_ptr.type, buffer_ptr.addr,
1378 llvm::Align(alignment), is_volatile);
1379#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
1380 auto load =
1381 builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(buffer_ptr.type, buffer_ptr.addr, alignment, is_volatile);
1382#else
1383 auto load = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(buffer_ptr.addr, alignment, is_volatile);
1384#endif
1385
1386 loads.push_back(load);
1387 return load;
1388 };
1389
1390 // Pass all indices into BufferAccessHelper. In CodeGenLLVM,
1391 // non-flat indices will result in an error in CreateBufferPtr, but
1392 // a subclass may override CreateBufferPtr.
1393 BufferAccessHelper(op->buffer, op->indices, value_dtype, make_load);
1394
1395 if (loads.size() == 1) {
1396 return loads[0];
1397 } else {
1398 llvm::Value* ret = llvm::UndefValue::get(DTypeToLLVMType(value_dtype));
1399 for (size_t i = 0; i < loads.size(); i++) {
1400 ret = builder_->CreateInsertElement(ret, loads[i], ConstInt32(i));
1401 }
1402 return ret;
1403 }
1404}
1405
1406llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op) {
1407 if (auto* ptr_op = op->op.as<OpNode>()) {
1408 auto call_op = GetRef<Op>(ptr_op);
1409 if (op->op.same_as(builtin_call_extern_) || op->op.same_as(builtin_call_pure_extern_)) {
1410 // call extern intrinsic
1411 ICHECK_GE(op->args.size(), 1U);
1412 auto global_symbol = Downcast<StringImm>(op->args[0]);
1413 return this->CreateCallExtern(GetType(GetRef<PrimExpr>(op)), global_symbol->value, op->args,
1414 true);
1415 } else if (op_attr_global_symbol_.count(call_op)) {
1416 // call extern if the op itself have a global symbol.
1417 return this->CreateCallExtern(GetType(GetRef<PrimExpr>(op)), op_attr_global_symbol_[call_op],
1418 op->args, false);
1419 } else {
1420 VLOG(2) << "CreateIntrinsic: " << GetRef<Call>(op);
1421 auto x = CreateIntrinsic(op);
1422 VLOG(2) << "CreateIntrinsic done";
1423 return x;
1424 }
1425 } else {
1426 ICHECK(op->op.as<GlobalVarNode>());
1427 LOG(FATAL) << "Do not yet support cross function call";
1428 return nullptr;
1429 }
1430}

1432llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const RampNode* op) {
1433 llvm::Value* vec = llvm::UndefValue::get(DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype));
1434 for (int i = 0; i < op->lanes; ++i) {
1435 vec = builder_->CreateInsertElement(
1436 vec, MakeValue(op->base + op->stride * make_const(op->stride.dtype(), i)), ConstInt32(i));
1437 }
1438 return vec;
1439}
1440
1441llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const ShuffleNode* op) {
1442 std::vector<llvm::Value*> vecs(op->vectors.size());
1443 int total_lanes = 0;
1444 for (int i = 0, e = op->vectors.size(); i < e; ++i) {
1445 vecs[i] = VisitExpr(op->vectors[i]);
1446 total_lanes += op->vectors[i].dtype().lanes();
1447 }
1448 llvm::Value* v0 = CreateVecConcat(vecs);
1449 std::vector<uint32_t> idx(op->indices.size());
1450 for (int i = 0, e = op->indices.size(); i < e; ++i) {
1451 const int64_t* val = as_const_int(op->indices[i]);
1452 ICHECK(val && *val >= 0 && *val < total_lanes) << "Shuffled indeces are suppose to be int, "
1453 << "but get " << op->indices[i] << "\n";
1454 idx[i] = *val;
1455 }
1456 llvm::Value* mask = llvm::ConstantDataVector::get(builder_->getContext(), idx);
1457 auto res = builder_->CreateShuffleVector(v0, llvm::UndefValue::get(v0->getType()), mask);
1458 // If the output is a single-element vector, convert it back to a scalar.
1459 if (idx.size() == 1) {
1460 res = builder_->CreateExtractElement(res, ConstInt32(0));
1461 }
1462 return res;
1463}

1465llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const BroadcastNode* op) {
1466 return CreateBroadcast(MakeValue(op->value), op->lanes);
1467}

1473void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) {
1474 DataType value_dtype = op->value.dtype();
1475 Var buffer_var = op->buffer->data;
1476
1477 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(op->value);
1478
1479 auto make_store = [this, value](TypedPointer buffer_ptr, int subelement_i, int alignment,
1480 bool is_volatile) {
1481 llvm::Value* to_store = value;
1482 if (subelement_i != -1) {
1483 to_store = builder_->CreateExtractElement(value, subelement_i);
1484 }
1485#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1486 return builder_->CreateAlignedStore(to_store, buffer_ptr.addr, llvm::Align(alignment),
1487 is_volatile);
1488#else
1489 return builder_->CreateAlignedStore(to_store, buffer_ptr.addr, alignment, is_volatile);
1490#endif
1491 };
1492
1493 // Pass all indices into BufferAccessHelper. In CodeGenLLVM,
1494 // non-flat indices will result in an error in CreateBufferPtr, but
1495 // a subclass may override CreateBufferPtr.
1496 BufferAccessHelper(op->buffer, op->indices, value_dtype, make_store);
1497}

1499void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) {
1500 ICHECK(is_zero(op->min));
1501 analyzer_->Bind(op->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(op->min, op->extent));
1502 if (op->kind == ForKind::kUnrolled) {
1503 LOG(WARNING) << "Unroll hint get ignore at CodeGenLLVM backend, "
1504 << " consider set unroll_explicit=True";
1505 } else {
1506 ICHECK(op->kind == ForKind::kSerial);
1507 }
1508 CreateSerialFor(MakeValue(op->min), MakeValue(op->extent),
1509 llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(GetLLVMType(op->extent), 1), op->loop_var, op->body);
1510}

1512void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const WhileNode* op) {
1513 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1514 auto* while_cond = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "while_cond", function_);
1515 auto* while_body = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "while_body", function_);
1516 auto* while_merge = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "while_merge", function_);
1517 builder_->CreateBr(while_cond);
1518 builder_->SetInsertPoint(while_cond);
1519 builder_->CreateCondBr(MakeValue(op->condition), while_body, while_merge);
1520 builder_->SetInsertPoint(while_body);
1521 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1522 builder_->CreateBr(while_cond);
1523 builder_->SetInsertPoint(while_merge);
1524}
1525
1526void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const IfThenElseNode* op) {
1527 llvm::Value* cond = MakeValue(op->condition);
1528 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1529 auto* then_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_then", function_);
1530 auto* end_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_end", function_);
1531 if (op->else_case.defined()) {
1532 auto* else_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_else", function_);
1533 builder_->CreateCondBr(cond, then_block, else_block);
1534 builder_->SetInsertPoint(then_block);
1535 this->VisitStmt(op->then_case);
1536 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1537 builder_->SetInsertPoint(else_block);
1538 this->VisitStmt(op->else_case);
1539 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1540 } else {
1541 builder_->CreateCondBr(cond, then_block, end_block, md_very_likely_branch_);
1542 builder_->SetInsertPoint(then_block);
1543 this->VisitStmt(op->then_case);
1544 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1545 }
1546 builder_->SetInsertPoint(end_block);
1547}

1549void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const AllocateConstNode* op) {
1550 auto data = op->data.value();
1551 auto array = NDArrayToLLVMArray(llvm_target_->GetContext(), data);
1552 std::string symbol_name = op->buffer_var->name_hint;
1553 llvm::GlobalVariable* param_symbol = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
1554 *module_, array->getType(), true, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, array, symbol_name);
1555
1556 var_map_[op->buffer_var.operator->()] = param_symbol;
1557 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1558}

1560void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const AllocateNode* op) {
1561 ICHECK_EQ(op->extents.size(), 1)
1562 << "LLVM codegen only supports flat 1-d buffer allocation, but allocation of "
1563 << op->buffer_var->name_hint << " is " << op->extents << "-d";
1564
1565 ICHECK(!is_zero(op->condition));
1566 llvm::Value* buf = nullptr;
1567
1568 int32_t constant_size = op->ConstantAllocationSize();
1569 ICHECK_GT(constant_size, 0) << "Can only handle constant size stack allocation";
1570 StorageInfo& info = alloc_storage_info_[op->buffer_var.get()];
1571 if (constant_size % 4 == 0 && info.alignment == 0) {
1572 info.alignment = GetTempAllocaAlignment(op->dtype, constant_size);
1573 }
1574 // maximum necessary alignment in the NV devices
1575 if (info.alignment > 16) {
1576 info.alignment = 16;
1577 }
1578 llvm::AllocaInst* alloca = WithFunctionEntry([&]() {
1579 return builder_->CreateAlloca(DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype), ConstInt32(constant_size));
1580 });
1581#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1582 auto alignment = static_cast<unsigned>(alloca->getAlign().value());
1583#else
1584 unsigned alignment = alloca->getAlignment();
1585#endif
1586 if (alignment < static_cast<unsigned>(info.alignment)) {
1587#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
1588 alloca->setAlignment(llvm::Align(info.alignment));
1589#else
1590 alloca->setAlignment(info.alignment);
1591#endif
1592 }
1593#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1594 info.alignment = static_cast<unsigned>(alloca->getAlign().value());
1595#else
1596 info.alignment = alloca->getAlignment();
1597#endif
1598
1599 buf = alloca;
1600
1601 buf = builder_->CreatePointerCast(
1602 buf, DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype)->getPointerTo(buf->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()));
1603 buf->setName(op->buffer_var->name_hint.c_str());
1604
1605 ICHECK(!var_map_.count(op->buffer_var.get()));
1606 var_map_[op->buffer_var.get()] = buf;
1607 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1608}

1610void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
1611 if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent) {
1612 IterVar iv = Downcast<IterVar>(op->node);
1613 if (iv->thread_tag.length() != 0) {
1614 if (!var_map_.count(iv->var.get())) {
1615 var_map_[iv->var.get()] = GetThreadIndex(iv);
1616 analyzer_->Bind(iv->var, Range::FromMinExtent(0, op->value));
1617 }
1618 }
1619 } else if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::storage_alignment) {
1620 const VarNode* v = op->node.as<VarNode>();
1621 ICHECK(v);
1622 alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment = static_cast<int>(op->value.as<IntImmNode>()->value);
1623 if (var_map_.count(v) && alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment > 1) {
1624 builder_->CreateAlignmentAssumption(*data_layout_, GetVarValue(v),
1625 alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment);
1626 }
1627 } else if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::volatile_scope) {
1628 const VarNode* v = op->node.as<VarNode>();
1629 ICHECK(v);
1630 volatile_buf_.insert(v);
1631 }
1632 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1633}

1636 With<arith::ConstraintContext> cctx(analyzer_.get(), op->condition);
1637 this->VisitStmt(op->body);

1640void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) {
1641 const VarNode* v = op->var.get();
1642 ICHECK(!var_map_.count(v));
1643 if (v->dtype.is_handle()) {
1644 if (!is_restricted_) {
1645 alias_var_set_.insert(v);
1646 }
1647 }
1648 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(op->value);
1649 value->setName(v->name_hint.c_str());
1650 var_map_[v] = value;
1651 analyzer_->Bind(op->var, op->value);
1652 if (alloc_storage_info_.count(v) && alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment > 1) {
1653 builder_->CreateAlignmentAssumption(*data_layout_, GetVarValue(v),
1654 alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment);
1655 }
1656 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1657}
